<div class="hero-unit">
        <h1>SiriProxy server</h1>
        <p>You can manage your local SiriProxy server from this page, it just needs to be available from internet and all you have to know is his ip adress, the administrator account name ,and of course the  relieving password.</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary btn-large">What is a SiriProxy Server ? &raquo;</a></p>
</div>

<div class="hero-unit">
        <h2>Manage connection with the server:</h2>
        <p>This will configure the secured connection with your server.</p>

        <form action="/setconnectconfig" method="post" accept-charset="utf-8">
			<input type="text" name="login" placeholder="Login">
			<input type="text" name="password" placeholder="Password">
    		<input class="xlarge disabled" type="text" placeholder="Server IP Adress" disabled />
			<input type="submit" value="Connect">
		</form>
		
		<p><a href="/test" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Test irb/Applescript/Appscript/osax Connection &raquo;</a></p>
		<p><a href="/testconnectssh" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Test SSH Connection &raquo;</a></p>
        
</div>

<div class="hero-unit">
        <h2>Execute actions on the server:</h2>
        <p>Use the basic functions or feel free to build your own</p>
        
        <div class="row">
        <div class="span4">
          
          <p><a class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Update Server gems from Git repo(s)/plugins &raquo;</a></p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Bundle Server gems from local plugin dir(s) &raquo;</a></p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Start Server &raquo;</a></p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Stop Server &raquo;</a></p>
          
        </div>
        <div class="span6">
          
          <form action="/siriproxyservercustomcmd" method="post" accept-charset="utf-8">
			<textarea class="input-xlarge" id="customcmd" name="customcmd" placeholder="Custom Command" rows="10"></textarea>
			<input type="submit" value="Run commmand">
		  </form>
          
        </div>
      </div>
        
</div>

